article.description: Freshman Ryan Stanley ran for three touchdowns and threw for another as Florida A&M kept Delaware State winless, 41-27 in a Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference game Saturday.
article.headline: Stanley's 4 TDs lead Florida A&M past Delaware St, 41-27
article.linkText: Stanley's 4 TDs lead Florida A&M past Delaware St, 41-27
article.story: DOVER, Del. -- Freshman Ryan Stanley ran for three touchdowns and threw for another as Florida A&M kept Delaware State winless, 41-27 in a Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference game Saturday. Stanley scored from 17-yards out to give the Rattlers (2-5, 2-2) a 10-0 lead in the first quarter, then scored from 9 yards out in the second to help send Florida A&M into intermission with a 20-14 advantage. He scored from a yard out, then found Montavius Williams from 8-yards out as part of a 21-0 start to the fourth quarter. Orlando McKinney picked off a Daniel Epperson pass at the goal line and returned it 100 yards for a touchdown to complete the Florida A&M scoring effort. Stanley was 15 of 29 passing for 204 yards and carried 12 times for 118 yards. Brycen Alleyne ran for 169 yards and two touchdowns on 20 carries to lead Delaware State (0-6, 0-3).
